headline: A Look At Danaher (DHR) Valuation After Earnings And 2026 Targets Reaffirm Growth Story
summary: Danaher (DHR) is back in focus after its latest earnings, where revenue met Wall Street expectations and bioprocessing plus diagnostics helped support the outlook alongside new 2026 growth and profit targets. See our latest analysis for Danaher. Danaher shares have been choppy around the latest earnings release, with a recent 1 day share price return of 1.35% and a 30 day share price return showing a 6.73% decline, while the 1 year total shareholder return of 4.14% points to relatively modest...
